
    THE taxi industry may refuse to take on the minimum wage set by the labour department. The South African National Taxi Council said the taxi industry was a unique sector and the department should consult operators before making any decisions. The labour department released the minimum wage for the taxi sector earlier this year. According to the department, drivers’ salaries should increase from R3 207 a month to R3 413. If the owner wants the driver to sleep over somewhere, he must be paid an allowance of R372 or be given accommodation. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsstY3BGO1V8t9FYBuRIzUkd0TRU9it7qD0uGbyeXcgy65UT-ynj_hIhDQP91D4OCL2SsdxdD31KzFJQiw5ArrV8R0QOR_WBN8yO6FYrRQxBu21b42niey07EV-Y5pHwZkoApYk_vx2KhaF_bh8oviGGUlLlRF1pFlNDL1DKOJA_NzFoXWqcRtOpwJjDtGYagbOyVHcNjrAayHYN76wPnrRQaeyaHbIpuO-CWJi24eucWDMuFzonBc7dyz0r05WB_kLm6kCPpm5ysNEKtDzMAYUpiEDC4QE\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzN28gLu7iCaHEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
